disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Cell Division.

blurb.value: Each time Zac hits an enemy with an ability, he sheds a chunk of himself that can be reabsorbed to restore Health. Upon taking fatal damage, Zac splits into 4 bloblets that attempt to recombine. If any bloblets remain, he will revive with an amount of Health depending on the Health of the surviving bloblets. Each bloblet has a percentage of Zac's maximum Health, Armor and Magic Resistance. This ability has a 5 minute cooldown.

description.value: Innate - The Secret Weapon: Zac gains increased percentage size equal to 1.5% of his bonus health, capped at 35% increased size at 2333.33 bonus health. Zac's size also reduces based on his missing health, down to 70% total size while at 0% health.

description2.value: Innate: Every time Zac damages at least one enemy with an ability, he sheds, depending on the ability, a number of chunks of himself to a nearby location, landing towards visible nearby enemy champions and lasting for 6 seconds.

description3.value: Both Zac and his enemies can interact with these chunks by being within 50 units of them: Zac can move over them to consume them, restoring 4 / 5 / 6 / 7% (based on Let's Bounce!'s rank) of his maximum health; enemies can move over them to destroy them.

description4.value: Periodically, upon taking fatal damage, Zac dispels all debuffs, sets his current health to 50%, and temporarily becomes untargetable, creating 4 uncontrollable bloblets that are briefly untargetable while splitting, each having 12% of Zac's maximum health, which move to Zac's final location over 8 / 7 / 6 / 5 / 4 (based on level) seconds. If any of these bloblets remain alive until the end of the duration, Zac recombines and returns at 10 - 50% maximum health.

description5.value: Upon splitting, the bloblets stop upon colliding with terrain.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Zac's increased size does not consider his base stats, but does consider Gargoyle Stoneplate's increased base health. Cell Division's chunks spawn in two versions: Contestable: They will fall to the ground between Zac and the nearest visible enemy champion within 1000 range of him (dropping slightly in Zac's favor). Cannot be interacted with for the first 0.25 seconds (except during Let's Bounce!). Uncontestable: They will fall to the ground near Zac and can be picked up immediately (version used by default). Guardian Angel and Chronoshift will take precedence over Cell Division. Spirit Visage and  Heal Power increases the healing of both chunks and bloblets. Ryze's Realm Warp is able to individually teleport Zac or his bloblets during Cell Division. If Zac is transported to a new location before the bloblets landed, they will travel to form at his new position, adjusting their speed accordingly. If Cell Division's duration permits during this time, Zac will be revived even if the bloblets fail to recombine. Cell Division's bloblets can be targeted by Teleport and Syndra's Force of Will. Other bloblets are not interrupted by the conditions above and will continue to recombine instinctively. Zac's health when the bloblets are sent out is set to what it would be if all bloblets recombined, and is actively updated when the bloblets take damage. If Zac's health is higher than it is supposed to be when the bloblets converge on him, his health will be set to the correct value.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Stretching Strikes.

blurb.value: Zac stretches an arm, grabbing an enemy. Attacking a different enemy will cause him to throw both targets towards each other.

description.value: Active: Zac stretches his left arm in the target direction, dealing magic damage and slowing the first enemy hit by 40% for 0.5 seconds, and attaching it to the target for 2 seconds and revealing them for the duration while the tether persists.

leveling.value: Magic Damage:»40 / 55 / 70 / 85 / 100 (+ 30% AP) (+ 2.5% of Zac's maximum health)«Total Magic Damage:80 / 110 / 140 / 170 / 200 (+ 60% AP) (+ 5% of Zac's maximum health)

description2.value: While his arm is attached, his next basic attack is replaced by a second Stretching Strike and gains  200 range, dealing the same magic damage and slow after a 0.25-second cast time, but without being able to critically strike.

description3.value: If the two Stretching Strikes affect different targets, he roots both targets for 0.5 seconds and then flings them towards each other for 300 range.

description4.value: If the two targets are near each other, they're instead slammed against each other, both taking the initial magic damage and applied the slow again and also becoming stunned for 0.25 seconds.

Only necessary if the value differs from Unstable Matter.

blurb.value: Zac's body erupts, damaging nearby enemies.

description.value: Active: Zac's body explodes outward, dealing magic damage to all nearby enemies, capped against minions and monsters.

leveling.value: Magic Damage:»25 / 40 / 55 / 70 / 85 (+ 4 / 5 / 6 / 7 / 8% (+ 2% per 100 AP) of target's maximum health)«Capped Damage:225 / 240 / 255 / 270 / 285

description2.value: Zac grants ghosting to monsters hit for 5 seconds.

description3.value: Unstable Matter's  cooldown is reduced by 1 second every time Zac picks up a Cell Division chunk.

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Elastic Slingshot.

blurb.value: Zac attaches his arms to the ground and stretches back, launching himself forward.

description.value: Active: Zac charges up to 4.5 seconds, increasing Elastic Slingshot's  range over a cone in the target direction. Elastic Slingshot can be recast at any time within its duration.

description2.value: If Zac cancels the channel himself, or the charge completes without reactivation, 50% of Elastic Slingshot's  health cost and  cooldown are refunded.

description3.value: Recast: Zac dashes to the target location, dealing magic damage to all nearby enemies on impact and knocking them up for 0.5 − 1 (based on duration of the charge) seconds.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Let's Bounce!.

description.value: Passive: Increases Cell Division's healing from chunks.

leveling.value: Chunk Healing:5 / 5.5 / 6 / 6.5 / 7% of his maximum health

description2.value: Active: Zac bounces 4 times over 3 seconds, gaining 20% − 50% (based on duration)  bonus movement speed, but becoming unable to declare basic attacks and use Stretching Strikes and Elastic Slingshot for the duration. There is a 1-second delay between each bounce.

description3.value: Each bounce deals magic damage to all nearby enemies, knocking them back for 1 second and subsequently slowing them by 20% for the same duration.

description4.value: Enemies can be damaged by multiple bounces, with each beyond the first dealing 50% damage but not displacing them.
